-- Sarkozy’s Approval Rate Rises From Lows as Vote Nears, Poll Says
-- B y   G r e g o r y   V i s c u s i
-- 2012-02-13T16:01:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-13/sarkozy-s-approval-rate-rises-from-lows-as-vote-nears-poll-says.html
French President  Nicolas Sarkozy ’s
approval rating rose in February as he prepared to announce that
he’s running for re-election, according to a poll by Ipsos SA
for Le Point magazine.  Sarkozy’s rating, which hit a low of 29 percent last April,
rose two points during February to 36 percent. His disapproval
rating fell three points to 60 percent. The pollster questioned
974 people on Feb. 10-11. No margin of error was provided.  France  holds two rounds of presidential elections on April
22 and May 6.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gregory Viscusi in Paris at 
 gviscusi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
